# Agentx core

Follow `AGENTS.md` in this repo (or the project that imported Agentx).

## Always

- Follow `src/ai-context.md` for architecture & conventions
- Reuse long-lived branches (`main` / `testing` / `agentx`) — do **not** create a new branch per feature unless the user asks
- Commit / push / merge to `main` only when the user asks (then it is allowed)
- One writer per file/module
- Verify (build/tests) before claiming done; if you can’t run checks, say so
- Prefer small, reviewable changes over big dumps
- Do not silently invent the tech stack — use `agentx-lead` + **AskQuestion** (clickable choices, always include **Other**) when tools are undecided

## Before coding

1. **Lead gate** (`agentx-lead`) when stack is unclear, work is greenfield, or feature is sensitive (auth, payments, personal data, storage).
2. **Plan** (`agentx-plan`) when the work spans many files, needs parallel agents, or changes architecture / data / deps.

## Ending or switching work

Use skill `agentx-handoff` so the next session doesn’t guess.

## Isolation lanes (pick one)

| Lane | Use when |
|------|----------|
| Local checkout | Default single task |
| `/worktree` | 2+ local agents that must not collide |
| Cloud agent | Long / risky / overnight; full isolation |

Do not invent a multi-agent fleet unless the user asks. Default = one agent, one task, current checkout.
